<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Dematerialize sounds a lot like the invisibility of the mages in the "Recluse" series (basically the mage bends the light around him, so no one can see him, but he can't see anything, he can just use his magic sense to "feel" vaguely what is around him". I had thought of that as a way to add invisibility wihtout making it overpowering. Invis, but make it hard to get around or do much (e.g. clipping plane is really short, gamma goes way down, worse than night and torch won't work, other players and npc's aren't displayed, etc.) would make it a defensive tool for travel, recovery, etc. Or it could be a partial invis, so we appear more faint and ghostlike, and disappear from the clipping plane at a shorter range.<P>As for the illusions, I was only partially kidding, mostly about the straw man thing. Being able to look like a non caster would be pretty useful, again, while travelling (sniper might not bother to try a oneshot kill), or resting before and after fights. It should drop during combat like the run buffs though. I think the EQ pvp enchanters were causing major damage until they made the illusions drop upon casting offensive spells.<P>Merlin did use his magic to make Uther look like Igraine's husband (depending on which legend you read), so illusions would be in the realm of our possibiliies I should think.<P>--Winin
</FONT>
