<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I doubt this will ever fly.<P>1st, going inv is basically same thing as stealth.  So now we'll have stealth mezzers...imagine the chaos. =)<P>2nd, feather like movement to prevent falling damage, gee sounds like safe-fall of the rogues dont it?  <P>Not that I think there is anything wrong with rogue illusionist, as that is a popular AD&D multiclass and it fits very well, but just dont think it's gonna happen in DAoC. =)<P>I had an inspiration earlier, let's see what you guys think of it. <P>Body line spell.  Slow Damage Shield(for the lack of a better name)<P>This spell will absorb X amount of damage where X is your level multiplied by 10, maximum 500 points of damage.  (for explaination sake, let's say you are level 50)  Any damage taken beyond the limit will be immediately dealt.  As for the 500 absorbed points of damage, this spell will slow down your body's reaction towards damage.  It works like a powerful DoT spell that's casted on you (and would interrupt casting like a DoT).  It will deal out Y amount of damage every 2 seconds where Y is equal to your level.  DoT will expire as soon as all absorbed damage has been dealt.  Absorb will stop as soon as absorb limit is reached.  This spell will only work on damage taken above your level (50 points in this case) any lesser damage will be dealt normally.  <P>Scenario:  You just got criticaled by an archer for 700 points of damage.  You have 650hp at level 50 and your shield is on.  You will immediately take 250 damage, (700-500 absorbed + 50 immediate DOT damage) which puts you at 400hp, about 1/3 health.  Run like hell to your healer to get healed, he will have 14 seconds to react and heal.  If the sniper shoots you again for 200-300 you are good as dead anyways, but it does help prevent 1 shot kills.<P>This would help greatly in PvE as well.  The tanks/healer have about 3-4 swings of time to save your fragile behind instead of 1-2 swings. (1 swing BT, 2nd swing you are at half health) <P>For soloing, it lets you have a few more secs of time to run without being slowed down by lack of hp.<P>Looking back maybe the spell needs to be simplified, but the idea is to prolong life just a bit, which is what we want right?<P>Let me know what you guys think.<P>--------------------<P>Sephrenia Fairheart<BR>44 Sorceress of Guinevere<BR>34(43)mind/0(5)matter/30(35)body
</FONT>
