<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
It isn't an issue of coding, I assure you.  I could write nearly ever suggestion in this thread in under 45 minutes while a pack of wild wolverines disemboweled me.<P>The issue is, spells that have already been coded are already understood by the people trying to balance the game.  You go to someone and say, "Let's add an insta-cast PB AoE stun to sorcerers," and everyone is on the same page.  Make up a brand new spell and everyone will attempt to evaluate how powerful it is and if it can be abused.  Ultimately, they will probably decide not to implement a totally new spell just so they don't even have to bother figuring those questions out.<P>Sad, but very likely true, and not a condition unique to Mythic or the game industry either.<P>-Zanthis
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
